Player retribution against others.
 
This is about how Darkwind's player used punishment systems work.
If you vote to have someone pilloried or a bounty hunter to be
sent after them, then you are giving up your right to take
personal further action against that person unless they do
something else wrong.  If the person you voted for being pilloried
is pilloried, at that point, you have given up any other claim to
take further action against that person.  The purpose of the
player used punishment systems isn't so you can punish them three
times for one offense, it's for punishing them when you yourself
can't or are unwilling to take the job of retribution into your
own hands.  If a person has been, say pilloried, he has served his
punishment for his crime.  When players continue to harass him
afterward over it and in the end kill him, or send a bountyhunter
after him it will then be the killers that we will personally
frown upon and most likely take action against.  If you attempt
to take multiple methods of retribution against a player, you
will end up in just as bad a situation as the original offender
did.
 
It should also be pointed out that if you feel the need to hunt a
player to the ends of the earth as his punishment for doing
an action against you, that's fine, but once you use one of the
player punishment systems, you have given up the right to
further pursue the matter on your own.  Their purpose as
stated earlier isn't so you can have Darkwind punish the offender
while at the same time punish them yourselves.  It's so that you
can have the offender punished if you are incapable or unwilling
to do it yourself.
